(2) NASA launches mission to investigate a potentially habitable ocean worl=
d [ https://substack.com/redirect/903593f8-e878-4b46-950a-a80c0e12be68?j=3D=
eyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ]
Ashley Strickland for CNN
A mission to study one of the solar system=E2=80=99s most promising environ=
ments that may be suitable for life has lifted off. NASA=E2=80=99s Europa C=
lipper spacecraft =E2=80=94 designed to explore its namesake, Jupiter=E2=80=
=99s moon Europa =E2=80=94 launched aboard a SpaceX Falcon Heavy rocket Mon=
day at 12:06 p.m. ET from NASA=E2=80=99s Kennedy Space Center in Florida.
It=E2=80=99s SpaceX week. If they=E2=80=99d just done the catch, they would=
 have deserved two slots, but fortunately, they' did a second incredibly co=
ol, if more standard, thing.=20
Lost amidst the pomp and circumstance of the Starship catch, SpaceX was doi=
ng some real business last week too. A SpaceX Falcon Heavy launched NASA=E2=
=80=99s Europa Clipper spacecraft on Monday.=20
The aptly-named Europa mission will study Jupiter's moon, Europa, which has=
 one of the most promising environments for potential life in the solar sys=
tem. This particular moon is home to an ice-covered ocean, which may contai=
n conditions conducive to life. The craft is expected to arrive at Jupiter =
in 2030 and upon arrival it will conduct 49 flybys, analyzing its ocean's d=
epth, chemistry, and potential habitability.
We=E2=80=99ll be sure to report back in 2030 with the findings.=20
