ttps://substack.com/redirect/b940d105-2cfe-4dae-9c0d-c36d4e54b5a5?j=3DeyJ1I=
joiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ], =E2=80=9Ca new=
 village for families building the future.=E2=80=9D It will be located in w=
ine country 90 minutes north of SF, draw inspiration from Italian hill town=
s, and work off of five design principles:=20
Support a multi-generational community=20
Prioritize pedestrians & cyclists over cars=20
Cultivate a culture of learning & building=20
Protect & harmonize with nature=20
Promote health & wellness=20
Devon has been studying cities for years, and launched a popup - Edge Esmer=
elda - earlier this year, so maybe it=E2=80=99s not the case that anyone ca=
n start a town, but I love the fact that more and more people are just goin=
g for it.=20
Double Bonus: Cargo Airships are Happening [ https://substack.com/redirect/=
e08987af-5b5a-410d-be9e-828e47be0cdc?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNu=
aMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ]
by Eli Dourado =20
Nothing says =E2=80=9Cwe=E2=80=99re back=E2=80=9D like four ex-SpaceX engin=
eers teaming up to build massive airships. So=E2=80=A6 we=E2=80=99re back.=
=20
Eli Dourado has been obsessed with airships for a few years, culminating in=
 a very popular blog post last year titled Cargo airships could be big [ ht=
tps://substack.com/redirect/4a78f23d-80aa-4033-afc2-de2a6550e338?j=3DeyJ1Ij=
oiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ]. One of the peop=
le who read the blog post was Jim Coutre, who spent several years as an eng=
ineer at SpaceX before becoming the Chief Engineer at Hyperloop. After read=
ing it, Jim started a spreadsheet and worked what exactly it would take to =
build huge airships for cargo.=20
As Eli wrote in the follow-up =E2=80=94 Cargo airships are happening [ http=
s://substack.com/redirect/e08987af-5b5a-410d-be9e-828e47be0cdc?j=3DeyJ1Ijoi=
OXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ] =E2=80=94  Jim fou=
nd one discrepancy in Eli=E2=80=99s post. Eli said that Airships could be c=
heaper but slower than air freight. Jim realized that, when you take into a=
ccount the steps on either side of the plane, and design an Airship that ca=
n just hover over a customer=E2=80=99s facility to pickup goods on one side=
 and hover over a customer=E2=80=99s facility to dropoff goods on the other=
, airships can actually be faster than planes.=20
Better, faster, cheaper. That=E2=80=99s my music.=20
Luckily, Jim decided to build Airship Industries, and Eli introduced us. I=
=E2=80=99m positively buoyant to be able to back Jim and the Airship Indust=
ries team out of Not Boring Capital.=20
Follow Jim [ https://substack.com/redirect/a43fc598-a7b9-4671-a26a-c20927c3=
5fc0?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ] a=
nd Airship [ https://substack.com/redirect/94c57eed-80f3-4df8-99f0-cd142d0a=
04a9?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ] t=
o watch the progress in real-time. =20
Have a great weekend y=E2=80=99all.
